config_1.rationale: Small r/d to assess slower learning due to strong projection; baseline lr and participation.

config_2.rationale: Mid r/d expected sweet spot balancing convergence speed and projection benefit.

config_3.rationale: Large r/d approaching momentum SGD; tests diminished projection benefits.

config_4.rationale: Sweet-spot r/d with conservative lr to probe stability improvements.

config_5.rationale: Sweet-spot r/d with higher lr to test faster progress vs potential instability.

config_6.rationale: Sweet-spot r/d with higher participation to reduce aggregation variance and accelerate convergence.

config_7.rationale: Small r/d with more clients per round to compensate for slower learning via reduced variance.

config_8.rationale: Large r/d with fewer clients to explore drift and communication trade-offs under reduced participation.
